        <name>8.2.3.2 Exercise 3x3 linear system inverse matrix method</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consider the linear system of equations \(AX = B\), where &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;\[ A ={@matrixa@}, \hspace{2mm} B = {@BB@}. \]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol class="HELM_parts_inline"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find the inverse of \( A\), if it is invertible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;\(A^{-1}=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:Result]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;li&gt; Solve the system \(AX = B \) using the inverse matrix method.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;\(X=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:ans2]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt; We find the inverse of \( A \) using the Gauss elimination method (use the determinant method if you prefer). Augment matrix \({\bf A}\) with a 3 by 3 identity matrix:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[{@auga@}\]&lt;br&gt;There is&amp;nbsp; +1 in the upper left-hand corner so create 0's below it by adding \({@-mrow2@}\) times row 1 to row 2 and \({@-mrow3@}\) times row 1 to row 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[{@temp1@}\]&lt;br&gt;Now there is&amp;nbsp; +1 in entry [2,2] of the matrix so create 0's above and below it by adding \({@-mr1@}\) times row 2 to row 1 and \({@-mr3@}\) times row 2 to row 3&lt;br&gt;\[{@temp2@}\]&lt;br&gt;Now there is&amp;nbsp; +1 in entry [3,3] of the matrix
    so create 0's above it by adding \({@-mro1@}\) times row 3 to row 1 and \({@-mro2@}\) times row 3 to row 2&lt;br&gt;\[{@temp3@}\]&lt;br&gt;The left half of this matrix is the identity matrix and the right half is the inverse of \({\bf A}\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore \({\bf A^{-1}} = {@correctanswer@}\)&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Since \(A \) is invertible, we can apply the inverse matrix method to solve the system of equations. Multiply the matrix equation \(A X = B \) by \(A^{-1} \) from the left to obtain \[ X = A^{-1} A X = A^{-1} B = {@correctanswer@} {@BB@} = {@correctanswer
  . BB@}. \] &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
